@*
    Shared BREADCRUMB — REQUIREMENTS §21 cross-cutting ("breadcrumbs").

    Renders the organizer back-office ancestor trail for the current page —
    e.g. "Organizer area  /  People  /  Participants" — so a deep feature page
    (reached via a single collapsed nav dropdown) always shows where it sits and
    gives a one-click way back to its hub and the organizer root.

    Source of truth: the pure, unit-tested BreadcrumbBuilder (Core), which maps
    the request path to its ANCESTOR crumbs (root ▸ hub). The current page is NOT
    in that list — this partial appends ViewData["Title"] as the non-linked,
    aria-current leaf, so the leaf always matches the page title already set and
    no per-page wiring is needed.

    Accessibility:
      - <nav aria-label> + an ordered list (semantic trail order).
      - the current page is aria-current="page" and not a link.
      - the "/" separators are decorative (aria-hidden).
    Mobile-first: the trail wraps at ~360px (flex-wrap) with small tap targets.

    Renders nothing when there is no trail (non-organizer pages, the organizer
    root itself, or an unknown path), so it is safe to include on every page.
*@
@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Localization
@using CommunityHub.Core.Navigation
@inject IHtmlLocalizer<CommunityHub.Core.Resources.SharedResource> Localizer
@{
    var path = Context.Request.Path.Value;
    var trail = BreadcrumbBuilder.Build(path);
    var leaf = ViewData["Title"] as string;
}
@if (trail.Count > 0)
{
    <nav class="ceh-breadcrumb" aria-label="@Localizer["Breadcrumb.Label"]">
        <ol>
            @foreach (var crumb in trail)
            {
                <li>
                    <a href="@crumb.Href">@Localizer[crumb.LabelKey]</a>
                    <span class="ceh-breadcrumb__sep" aria-hidden="true">/</span>
                </li>
            }
            @if (!string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(leaf))
            {
                <li><span aria-current="page">@leaf</span></li>
            }
        </ol>
    </nav>
}
